cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with the process of discovering and blocking circumvention proxy servers. It also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) as the testing is done from different sites in the U.S., China, and Iran. The paper may also fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CY) as it deals with obfuscated Tor bridges. Additionally, the paper involves data structures (cs.DS) as it measures the delay between the discovery and blocking of proxies. Finally, the paper may also belong to the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it discusses the behavior of censors and their impact on threat modeling and evasion.
